title: For Sale/Trade:  Taurus Raging Bull 6" stainless 454 Casull
postcontent:
Im looking to trade all my 454 casull stuff. i have a 6" Taurus Raging Bull in 454 casull. it has been fired 25 times. I love the revolver but its not practical for the hog hunting we do. The package comes with the Raging bull, a set of lee reloading dies, a box of winchester factory ammo, 2 holsters, a box of brass, a scope mount and an ammo box. The brass i got from someone, most is new. he primed a few but i never loaded them so i do not know what primers are in the brass. the brass is from starline so it is small rifle primers. Magnum primers need to be used with all casull brass. the leather holster comes with the cartridge belt and then i also have a Bianchi holster for it. the scope mount is a weigand combat scope mount that is matched stainlss like the revolver with a set of weaver grand slam 1" medium scope rings.. in total i have 100 pieces of brass. You have everything needed to get out and hunt hogs with this and everything to get started reloading for the casull. 



Im mainly looking to trade for lever action rifles or single action pistols. I might take an AR-15. you can send offers, worst i can say is no. For lever actions i really want a 45 colt or 30-30 or both.

Trade and cash value must be close to $1000. its all worth well over that

title: For Sale:  SCAM: Rock River .458 SOCOM w/ storm case/160 rds ammo
location: Murrells Inlet, South Carolina, United States
postcontent:
BEWARE: the listing for a Rock River .458 socom w/ storm case/160 rds ammo is a SCAM. This is a fake listing and when you contact the seller they ask for you to send payment to a M. Gilliam in Murrells Inlet. Or they will ask you to send it to a person and address in Georgia and/or Jacksonville, FL. The person in SC that received the check is honest and found himself in the middle of a scam using his name and a fake email address. 
Photos of the fake gun for sale are attached. 
What to do: contact your loca FBI and AFT office to make them aware if you have been scammed. This is a federal felony once it crosses state lines and is wire fraud. 

If you are making a purchase from any website, always do it through a registered FFL dealer and gun store. Send payment to the dealer and they will forward the weapon after receiving it. If it is a scam, then you will get your money back because no weapon will have been dropped off. Always get an address and phone number from the seller and the FFL dealer and verify they are correct and contact the FFL license holder of that gun store.

Be smart out there and do things the right way and these scammers will not be able to feed off the innocent.

postcontent:
Smith & Wesson

Governor .410 Gauge/.45 Colt/.45 ACP 2.75" Barrel, Matte Black Finish, Synthetic Grip, Six Rounds Any Combination Of Calibers

Single action/double action. Heat treated scandium alloy frame, stainless PVD cylinder. Tritium night front sight, dovetailed. Fixed rear sight. SIX ROUNDS. THREE CALIBERS. 159 YEARS OF PROTECTION.

Introducing the S&W GOVERNOR.
 New. Versatile. Lightweight. The Smith & Wesson Governor revolver puts six rounds of customizable response under your control. Load with .410 2 1/2" shotshells, .45 ACP or .45 Colt - alone or in combination - and hit your target in every situation. Plus, it's from the leading expert in revolver manufacturing over the past 159 years. Now that's confidence.

From the Smith & Wesson Press Room

Smith & Wesson Corp., the legendary 159-year old company in the global business of safety, security, protection and sport, announced yesterday the introduction of the Governor - a new firearm engineered as the ultimate self-defense package.

January 19, 2011 SPRINGFIELD, Mass.

Offering multiple caliber capabilities along with a lightweight scandium alloy frame, the Governor carries forward Smith & Wesson's rich history of revolver manufacturing and dedication to the personal protection market. 

Named the Governor for its authoritative appearance and specialized features, this new revolver provides discerning consumers with an essential tool for self-defense needs. At the core of this revolver is Smith & Wesson's patented heat-treated scandium frame for superior strength and reduced weight. Capable of chambering a mixture of .45 Colt, .45 ACP and .410 gauge 2 ½-inch shotshells, the Governor is suited for both close and distant encounters, allowing users to customize the load to their preference. The shooter's choice of ammunition is housed in the revolver's six-shot stainless PVD-coated cylinder, which adds an extra level of protection to this already rugged platform. On top of the revolvers compact 2 ¾-inch barrel, Smith & Wesson has added a dovetailed Tritium front night sight for enhanced accuracy in low-light conditions, while the Governors fixed rear sight is aptly suited for this self-defense handgun.

The Governor measures 8 ½ inches in overall length along with a width of 1 ¾ inches. Carry ability of this revolver has been further enhanced with the Governor's unloaded weight of 29.6 ounces and standard matte black finish designed to reduce unwanted glare while adding an all-business like demeanor to this self-defense handgun. On the lower portion of the frame, the revolver will be packaged with either shock absorbing synthetic grips or with factory-installed laser grips from Crimson Trace. Accurate, rugged and reliable, the Governor is further enhanced by Smith & Wesson's renowned smooth double-action and crisp single-action trigger pull. The new revolver will also come standard with 2-round and 6-round moon clips.

"For 159 years, Smith & Wesson has been at the forefront of revolver manufacturing with its advanced techniques and ground-breaking designs", said James Debney, President of the Firearms Division for Smith & Wesson. With the advent of the new Governor, this pioneering mindset continues as does our unyielding commitment to produce and bring to market self-defense orientated products that match the needs of consumers. Along with our broad range of personal protection firearms, the new Governor will take a leadership role that will give consumers a distinct advantage when defending themselves against unwanted dangers."

title: For Sale/Trade:  Springfield Armory M1A and extras
postcontent:
I have up for sale or trade a Springfield Armory M1A. This is a Standard model rifle that was assembled in 2002 according to SA records. This was before they began using all civilian parts to build these rifles, so with the exception of the receiver, it's made with GI parts. It has a H&R 22" chrome lined barrel, which according to the stamping was produced in June of 1962. The bore and chamber are pristine, and it's rated for fully automatic fire (it was made for an M14). It has a synthetic stock that has a couple minor chips, but it's virtually impossible to find the milsurp stocks without blemishes. It will come with (4) steel 10 round magazines, (3) steel 20 round magazines, and (1) Thermold 20 round magazine. Also included is the SA 3rd gen scope mount, SA 6x ranging scope, and the M2 bipod.
